# Remote Work Role-Based Control System (RBCS)

## ğŸ“Œ Overview
The **Remote Work Role-Based Control System (RBCS)** is a secure access management platform designed to support remote and hybrid work environments. It controls user access to system resources based on assigned roles, ensuring that users can only perform actions permitted by their responsibilities.

This system enhances **security**, **accountability**, and **efficiency** for organizations with distributed teams.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives
- Enforce secure access control for remote workers  
- Prevent unauthorized access to sensitive resources  
- Simplify user and permission management  
- Improve operational efficiency in remote teams  

---

## ğŸ”‘ Key Features
- User authentication and authorization  
- Role-based access control (RBAC)  
- Multiple user roles with defined permissions  
- Secure login system  
- Admin dashboard for managing users and roles  
- Scalable and flexible for growing teams  

---

## ğŸ‘¥ User Roles
Typical roles supported include:

- **Admin**
  - Manage users and roles
  - Assign permissions
  - Full system access

- **Manager**
  - Access team resources
  - Monitor reports and activities

- **Employee**
  - Access assigned tools and data only

*(Roles can be customized based on organizational needs.)*

